    <para id="import-auto-id1169034248467">Hobbs, Frank. 1994. “The Elderly Population.” <emphasis effect="italics">Population Profile of the United States</emphasis>. Retrieved January 28, 2012 (<link url="http://www.census.gov/population/www/pop-profile/elderpop.html">http://www.census.gov/population/www/pop-profile/elderpop.html</link>).</para><para id="eip-6">The Japan Times. 2016. "Constitutional change may target Japan’s elderly." July 23, National.</para><para id="import-auto-id1169034248478">Lee, Mary. 2009. “Trends in Global Population Growth.” <emphasis effect="italics">Research Starters Sociology: Academic Topic Overview</emphasis>. Retrieved January 28, 2012 from (<link url="http://www.ebscohost.com/academic/academic-search-premier">http://www.ebscohost.com/academic/academic-search-premier</link>).</para><para id="import-auto-id1169034248490">Levy, Becca R., Martin D. Slade, Suzanne R. Kunkel, and Stanislav V. Kasl, 2002. “Longevity Increased by Positive Self-perceptions of Aging.” <emphasis effect="italics">Journal of Personality and Social Psychology</emphasis> 83(2):261–270.</para>
